{"id":"da-kh2","title":"MCP server spec: expose archive query + file retrieval to enterprise","description":"Design spec for DataArchive MCP server. Two capability tiers: (1) metadata queries against archive.db (search files, list drives, check dedup status), (2) file retrieval with local buffer cache (robocopy from F:/Z: into fast local storage, serve from cache). Consumers: CLI zgents, Claude Desktop, Cowork. Traffic profile: infrequent archival retrieval, batch-oriented, MB-scale, not latency-critical. Key files: Clipmate backups, GMailTakeout, selective SQL backups at meaningful schema-change points. Cache: simple LRU or manual cleanup, no streaming needed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"steve@juststeve.com","created_at":"2026-04-12T20:54:56Z","created_by":"Steve","updated_at":"2026-04-14T09:06:57Z","closed_at":"2026-04-14T09:06:57Z","close_reason":"MCP server implemented and shipped. 5 tools (search_files, list_drives, drive_summary, get_file, check_hash) over stdio with @modelcontextprotocol/sdk. 16 tests passing. Windows launcher with DA_CACHE_PATH fix. Registered via .mcp.json. All smoke tests against real archive.db succeeded. Minor polish items (path-traversal guard, graceful DB close, unused isCached) deferred as nice-to-haves.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"da-9oc","title":"Fix populate_hashes.py schema mismatch and WSL path join","description":"populate_hashes.py INSERT targets columns (quick_hash, sha256_hash, file_path, file_size) that don't exist in the real file_hashes table (which has hash_type, hash_value, computed_at). Also path join uses backslash which breaks on WSL /mnt/ paths. Fix both, then run SHA-256 hashing for DVRC scan 33 to enable cross-drive dedup in harvest plan.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"steve@juststeve.com","created_at":"2026-04-12T18:18:25Z","created_by":"Steve","updated_at":"2026-04-12T21:56:28Z","closed_at":"2026-04-12T21:56:28Z","close_reason":"Fixed populate_hashes.py: rewrote to match real file_hashes schema (hash_type/hash_value/computed_at), fixed WSL path join, SHA-256 only. Ran against DVRC scan 33: 810k files hashed, 155k dup groups found. Regenerated harvest manifest with dedup: 62k files deduped, copy target reduced from 194k to 132k files (161→158 GB). Also created C:\\Tools\\harvest.cmd launcher.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"da-7pq","title":"_init_schema() drives CREATE TABLE is missing drive_code (schema drift vs migrations)","description":"## Bug\n\n`python/core/database.py` `_init_schema()` (around lines 102-123) runs on every `Database.__init__` and executes a `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS drives (...)` that defines 15 columns but omits `drive_code`. The real production db at `data/archive.db` has `drive_code` because it was added later via an ALTER TABLE migration applied by `python/apply_migrations.py`. There may be other post-v1 columns similarly missing — a full audit via `PRAGMA table_info` on the live db vs. the CREATE TABLE statement would confirm the full extent of drift.\n\n## Consequence\n\nAny code path that creates a fresh `archive.db` (e.g. running `scan_drive.py` from a cwd where the `--db` path doesn't exist yet) produces a schema-drifted db missing `drive_code`. Subsequent INSERTs referencing `drive_code` blow up with:\n\n```\nsqlite3.OperationalError: table drives has no column named drive_code\n```\n\n## How it was triggered\n\nDiscovered 2026-04-11 during DataArchive-y50 (C: boot drive scan). `scan_drive.py` was launched with cwd=`python/` and default `--db data/archive.db`, which resolved to a fresh `python/data/archive.db` instead of the real `/root/projects/DataArchive/data/archive.db`. The stray db was auto-created by `_init_schema()` with the broken schema, and the scan crashed twice on drive INSERT.\n\n## Fixes\n\nTwo options:\n\n**(a)** Sync the `CREATE TABLE` in `_init_schema` to match current production schema. Simple but brittle — any future column adds must be made in two places, and we already know drift has happened once undetected.\n\n**(b) (recommended)** Route fresh-db creation through `apply_migrations.py` so migrations always run after base schema creation. More durable — single source of truth for schema evolution, and covers the likely case that other post-v1 columns have drifted too.\n\n## Related\n\n- DataArchive-y50 (discovery context — C: boot drive scan crash)\n- `python/core/database.py` `_init_schema()` ~line 102\n- `python/apply_migrations.py` (reconciliation path)","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"steve@juststeve.com","created_at":"2026-04-11T20:32:57Z","created_by":"Steve","updated_at":"2026-04-11T20:32:57Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
